reviews.review: Such a stellar cast and a great script. It kept me guessing and in suspense to see where it would take me next. Overall a great take on the classic Whodunnit? formula.

Wow Rian Johnson. He has come out with a fascinatingly thrilling, fast-paced and nostalgic murder mystery. The cast is bloody brilliant and perform their roles perfectly in this stylistic fictional world that Johnson has created.
 
Everything about this movie is beautiful. Not much can be said about other than it is the perfect genre movie. Absolutely excellent from all involved.
Solid movie, minus the political undertones. Not many whodunnit type movies anymore, it’s an interesting figure it out type story. Didn’t like Craig’s accent though, that was kinda weird.
It was great - it didn't feel like over two hours because of the casting and Daniel Craig's so-bad-it's-good Southern accent. Great plot, good twists, I enjoyed this.
Eh, if they hadn't interjected political commercials, it might have been better - but either way, it was still very predictable.
One of the best mystery film for a long time

I went into this film trying to not like it because of the unforgivable job that Rian Johnson did with The Last Jedi, but I came out of this film in awe! Knives Out is a wonderful piece of cinema and an enjoyable who-done-it ride that everyone should see - unless they are a young child of course. 

All of the characters are interesting, and the film is well-written and directed. I thought I figured out what was going to happen in the film, but I was completely wrong. Rian found a film that he could rightfully subvert expectations on and it turned out wonderfully. 

Rian has proved that his films are worth watching, but I still will not forgive him.

My Rating: A+

We loved this movie! It looked good from the previews but it was much better than I expected. It was suspenseful at times, had good twists and turns, and was actually really funny too! I would definitely recommend it.
